Full Description: Dial91.com is one of the largest telephone calling card companies serving the India market.  Calls can be placed at a discount to all countries of the world, but the specialty of Dial91.com is India. The company has 24/7 support which includes live telephone support operators in the US and India, chat, online, email and fax. The unique niche that Dial91.com occupies is providing a very high quality phone connection at a very low price per minute.  The company does not use "gimmicks" to inflate the price of the call as almost all other companies do.  So although their base rate per minute may appear slightly higher then the competition, without the gimmicks the rate is virtually always lower. The company has experienced phenomenal growth since beginning business in 2007.  They feel that this is due to their strategy of 1. high quality telephone connections; 2. low price per minute rates; 3. superior customer service including guaranteed 100% correct billing; and 4. the latest and greatest feature set for convenient calling. The company has also developed iPhone and Android apps that make calling India extremely convenient.  These apps do not use cell minutes so the cost is reduced further.

Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: 94Fifty is a Bluetooth-enabled basketball that measures consecutive dribbles, dribble power, shot speed, arc, and backspin. This smart sensor basketball uses its patented point-of-force technology to help athletes more rapidly develop muscle-memory. The basketball measures key motor skills, learns the strengths and weaknesses of players at any level, and adapts as the player improves.  While wearing Glass, basketball players receive visual and audio shot feedback in real time for skills including shot arc, shot release speed, and backspin.  With a range of over 100 yards, the basketball communicates with Glass via bluetooth to display key metrics necessary to build better shooting skills. The Glassware includes three key shooting analyses tools: Shot Arc Analyzer, Shot Release Speed Timer, and Shot Backspin Analyzer. The Glassware instantly overlays shooting data into the field of view for the shooter or coach, helping the user visualize the quality of each shot.  The data makes it easier for the player to adjust mechanics, improve shooting range, develop a softer shot, or simply become a better free throw shooter. It can be used by the coach watching the player, or by the player practicing on his or her own. 94Fifty has also introduced apps that are now available for Glass, iOS 7, and Android, which provides athletes the ability to share their achievements with friends, family, and coaches via social media. 4Fifty Smart Sensor Basketball is the official smart basketball of the National Association of Basketball Coaches and has been endorsed by the Amateur Athletic Union Basketball (AAU).

Description: Heartbroker is an online dating site that incorporates objective feedback from trusted friends to determine compatibility between matches.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Heartbroker is the first and only dating site that uses objective feedback from trusted friends to determine compatibility between potential matches.  The biggest problem with online dating today is that people often misrepresent themselves in their profile. Sometimes this is unintentional; it is difficult to be objective when evaluating oneself. Other times, members use "harmless" white lies to seem more attractive. There is even an entire industry devoted to enhancing people's profiles to make them more attractive. Even worse, scammers and predators use online dating to take advantage of unsuspecting people. We decided there had to be a better way and we found it by going back to a method that has been around for centuries. Before online dating, people were commonly introduced through family or friends. These introductions provided a social filter; a friend that knows you offers a unique perspective about who is or isn't a good fit for you. It also keeps people honest; a married person masquerading as single is very unlikely to be recommended by his friends. We realized that that the idea of using a social context to improve the matchmaking process meshed perfectly with the rise in popularity of social networks like Facebook.  Thus, Heartbroker was born. Heartbroker's mission: to be the single best way for you to find a compatible match. These values act as guiding principles for our business: 1.Treat our users and community the way we would want to be treated. 2.Deliver a valuable service that is worth the price. 3.Respect the privacy and sensitivity of our users. 4.Life is short, so enjoy the ride.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Events, Internet Services

Description: JobOn is an online recruitment platform that enables hiring managers to review video responses to interview questions by job applicants.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: JobOn enables employers to reduce the time spent finding and hiring hourly staff by 75%.   For retail, restaurant and hospitality firms with high turnover, recorded video via webcam or mobile device simplifies the interview and hiring process, and lowers recruitment costs.  This happens because the most important part of hiring for these jobs is the interview, so JobOn has reversed the traditional process.  Eliminating the paper application in which it's difficult to distinguish applicants, JobOn essentially puts the interview first and helps managers make better, faster decisions about who to bring in for a face-to-face interview and who to hire.  No longer do walk-in applicants compete with customers for a manager's attention, nor do seekers have to fill out multiple applications all over town.  Now it's a matter of borrowing the speed dating concept and applying it online to potential employees and hiring managers.
